@host = http://localhost:3000
@apiKey = <your-api-key>

### 1. Health check (no auth — sits above the apiKeyAuth gate)
GET {{host}}/health

### 2. Create a subscription pointing at the local receiver
POST {{host}}/subscriptions
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "target_url": "http://localhost:4000/hook",
  "event_type": "employee.terminated"
}

### 3. Ingest an event (named so the next request can read its response)
# @name ingestEvent
POST {{host}}/events
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
content-type: application/json
idempotency-key: demo-terminated-001

{
  "event_type": "employee.terminated",
  "payload": { "employee_id": 42, "last_day": "2026-06-23" }
}

### 4. See what happened to that event — event_id chained from request #3
GET {{host}}/events/{{ingestEvent.response.body.$.event_id}}/deliveries
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

### 5. Subscription on a FAILING endpoint (distinct event_type) — demo retries + dead-letter
POST {{host}}/subscriptions
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "target_url": "http://localhost:4000/hook?fail=1",
  "event_type": "employee.suspended"
}

### 6. Ingest an event for the failing subscription — watch attempt_count climb, then dead-letter
# @name ingestFailing
POST {{host}}/events
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
content-type: application/json
idempotency-key: demo-suspended-001

{
  "event_type": "employee.suspended",
  "payload": { "employee_id": 99, "reason": "policy_violation" }
}

### 7. (bonus) Track the failing event's deliveries — re-Send this to watch the retries
GET {{host}}/events/{{ingestFailing.response.body.$.event_id}}/deliveries
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
